##Diary of an infected area: from medical care to patients, my life and death from self-help special report

Micro Signal Xincaijing

Function introduction, the recorder of new business, the promoter of New Economy.

-- To Yuen Yuen

Edit single

A new outbreak of coronary pneumonia is expected in a week's time. The outbreak has been going on for two months since it was discovered in early December.

Throughout, the medical staff have been the most frontline of the retrograde. Wuhan, a newly emerging first-tier city, has become the most brutal war zone in China.

The front line medical staff has been working overtime since the sound of the charge, the wards are full, supplies are scarce, the national fight against COVID-19 is still going on, and the medical staff are working in their own way, to keep the city running.
Where there's a battle, there's a wound.

In the early days of the campaign, medical workers contracted new coronary pneumonia without even knowing it; even now, they remain the most at risk.

Save him and save yourself simultaneously.

The following is an oral account of the Wuhan Front Line of the "fight against the epidemic" by the four COVID-19 medical staff. (collated by Zincic Finance and Economics Editor)

"separated from her lover on both sides of the Yangtze River, everything will be fine. "

Narrator: Dr. Ye of Wuhan No. 7 Hospital

Infection was confirmed on January 30,2020

In 2003, I sat for the National College Entrance Examination, the year that global attention was drawn to the SARS virus that first appeared in Guangdong. At that time, the university entrance examination two days to take the temperature to enter the examination room, some candidates are not feeling well, surrounded by medical and security guards.

After the college entrance examination, I filled in the Medical College of Wuhan University, and now I am a doctor in the Seventh Hospital of Wuhan City. Unexpectedly, in 2020, Wuhan as the center of the Coronavirus Storm, I also became the center of the Vortex.

On January 21,2020, the Seventh Hospital of Wuhan City was selected as a designated admission hospital, and the hospital immediately carried out environmental rectification and vacated all beds for admission to the hospital for the treatment of confirmed and suspected cases of pneumonia caused by COVID-19 infection.

At 10 p.m. on Jan. 22, patients lined up on the street, and within two hours, the hospital wards were full. Faced with such a situation, as a first-line medical staff, frankly, there is a bit nervous, but put on the work clothes, we are more busy, busy fighting the virus, busy and time scramble.

The paramedics are too busy fighting the virus

January 24th is Glittering Days's Eve and my sleepless night.

The night shift, from 5 p.m. to 8:30 a.m. , saw nearly 300 patients a night, worked nonstop for nearly 16 hours, and, in addition to the high risk of infection, had many more difficulties than anyone could have imagined.

The protective materials in the hospital were in short supply, and the protective clothing on everyone could not be taken off before the end of the shift. At that time, we had no experience. After putting on the protective clothing, we didn't eat or drink, and we didn't go to the bathroom until 16 hours later, the first time we went through something like this, we panicked, and the next day we put on a diaper.

On the night of the first day of the Lunar New Year, it was another battle from dark to light. In the 16 hours, I saw hundreds more patients. January 26, the second day of the Lunar New Year, is "preparing" I noticed physical discomfort, CT imaging was positive, I was hit. In order to avoid becoming a source of infection, the hospital applied for isolation, January 30, NUCLEIC ACID test results came out, since then confirmed infection.

I chose to go home isolation treatment, every day there are many patients to see a doctor, I think their situation is still relatively optimistic, do not want to take up hospital beds, chose to go home.

Not only me, our hospital has more than 10 medical staff confirmed, most of us have chosen to isolate at home, built a small group of mutual care, exchange of ideas.

Here, in "the patient, " there's another person I care about most -- my lover.

She is also a first-line medical staff, also in the work was infected, she began isolation treatment January 22, January 30 was diagnosed, has been a serious illness, can only be treated in hospital isolation.

We haven't seen each other since we took her to the hospital on the 22nd. I was in Wuchang District, she was in Qiaokou District, across the Yangtze River, and I couldn't get across, and she couldn't come back, so we had to meet on video.

"It's all right, keep treating and you'll be fine. We'll see each other when she gets home, " I kept telling myself.

The two of us are most grateful, are infected at the end of the year, just a first-grade daughter on winter vacation was taken home by the parents, the family is now very healthy.

High-intensity work and the risk of infection, for us, it's all part of the job. The only thing that saddens me is the frequent occurrence of medical injuries. At midnight on New Year's Eve, I asked my colleagues to take a photo for me in the office to wish for New Year greetings. That is, I hope that more people can see our positive attitude, we're in the plague zone, but we're not afraid. Everything's GonNa be okay.

My mental state is much better now, and my soreness is getting better. I set myself the task of isolation: to ensure a healthy diet and keep my body temperature under control.

"We used diapers to keep the suits on longer. "

Narrator: A surgeon in a hospital in Wuhan, Li Zhao

Infection was confirmed on 26 January 2020

On the morning of January 17, I was on duty in the ward when an outpatient was transferred to a patient with low fever accompanied by abdominal discomfort. The patient had no respiratory symptoms, and he had not taken his own temperature, so we took him in normally.

At that time, Wuhan epidemic has not broken out, the social news is relatively stable, so we do not do anything to protect the general ward. Until the patient's chest x-ray, chest CT results, we found that there is a problem, it is likely to be latent pneumonia patients.

We've got to put her in isolation, put her on hold, or we're GONNA put more people at risk. I think I got it right after the exposure, right up to the 20s. I started to feel a bit out of sorts, so I immediately reported it to the department and put myself in isolation.

I didn't dare to go back to my home, just as my parents'apartment in Wuhan was empty, so I moved into the old couple's house by myself, self-isolation. Then there are the symptoms, first a cough, then a headache and fatigue.

Wuhan's epidemic situation and public sentiment probably broke out on the 21st and 22nd. With the rapid increase in the number of pneumonia and fever cases in the outpatient and emergency departments, the hospitals were short of materials and personnel.

Wuhan Hankou Hospital / Tuyuan Network

Some doctors and nurses use diapers, or are afraid to eat, or just eat a few crackers, to make a suit last longer.

In fact, our first line is the first to feel the crisis, I and colleagues chat in private, I think the situation in Wuhan is not very optimistic. So I early in our group of classmates, told them in the field are not to go back to Wuhan.

My family was also going to take a bus home to Hunan Province for the new year, but on the 22nd, the suspected patient was diagnosed. Not only can I not walk, I also dare not send my family to walk, went back, worried that home may have the risk of infection.

So my family decided to stay in Wuhan and spend the New Year separately. My wife and kids live together, and I'm all alone in my parents'house.

On New Year's Eve, we made a video call. At the time, I was pretty upset. I feel like I can't go home, I can't go to work, and I don't know if I'm really infected.

I was diagnosed on the 26th, but to tell you the truth, back at the hospital, in the isolation ward, I was really relieved. After a good rest and reassuring treatment, perhaps, such as the generation of antibody protection, can return to work to the front line to better support colleagues.

"My lover never came to see me at the front, so I wouldn't waste my suit. "

Narrator: Director of the Department of Radiology Wuhan Hankou Hospital, deputy chief physician, the first emergency team expert group members, he Jia'an

Confirmed infection January 22,2020

My colleagues and I have been at the forefront of the fight against pneumonia of unknown origin in Wuhan since early January. From the clearance of pneumonia of unknown cause in the South China Seafood Market to our hospital becoming one of the three designated hospitals in Wuhan, the hospital hall is full, the virus wreaks havoc, everything comes too suddenly, Menglie.

My CT department is at the forefront of lung screening, and since mid to late January, my colleagues and I have been seeing hundreds of patients a day, nearly half of them with unusual signs of viral lung infections. Because at that time, Wuhan Health Commission concluded that "limited human to human transmission" , our medical staff protection is not in place, until the hospital laboratory, pharmacy and other departments have doctors have fever and other symptoms, we realized the seriousness of the problem.

On the night of January 21, I began to have a fever and a dry cough. As a precaution, on the 22nd, I had a CT scan in my office, and the minute I got it, I knew I was infected, and I've seen so many similar images of patients these days. At that time reported to the hospital office, as a suspected case of isolation measures were taken.

Medical personnel involved in the treatment of new-type pneumonia

On the 26th, my nucleic acid test came back positive and I was officially diagnosed with COVID-19 pneumonia.

The first thing I did when I entered the isolation ward was to call my relatives back home. My wife was the director of the intensive-care unit at the hospital and also the deputy chief physician. I was sick and she was still fighting on the front lines, we have a 13-year-old daughter at home who has no one to care for her.

On the phone, I asked my relatives to take the children home. January 24, New Year's Eve, this is the first of the three of us can not reunite the Spring Festival, the children in their hometown, I in the hospital ward isolation, my wife outside the ward to see a doctor.

My wife and I are in the same hospital, but she hasn't come to see me in a week of isolation, and she said, "don't waste a suit. ".

I don't blame her, because the hospital's protective clothing is in short supply, and as you can see on the Internet and the news, many of my colleagues try to control themselves by not eating, not drinking, not going to the bathroom, and wearing protective clothing eight hours a day, one shirt at a time.

The Hankou Hospital has about 300 frontline staff, most of whom have never returned home from combat and have spent time either in hospital or in hotels near the hospital.

I currently live with a colleague. There are five staff members in the hospital who have been diagnosed with the infection. I am seriously ill. Physically, I still have a high fever and cough repeatedly. I need hormone injections in the morning and can get rid of the fever in the afternoon, sometimes at night the body temperature will rebound and rise, this disease no specific medicine, currently rely on hard anti-and some auxiliary treatment.

In my spare time, I talk to my daughter, and we never talk about it. My lung infection more and more serious, but also dare not tell my daughter and the elderly at home, looking at the hospital office to staff family letters, I will also quietly shed tears.

In this epidemic, there are many enterprises for health care workers to provide the corresponding protection policy, such as Ali and Alipay, for health care workers to set up a "health insurance fund" , unfortunately infected with the new type of coronary pneumonia, will provide us with an extra layer of security.

Now, inside and outside the hospital, women, children, ear, nose, throat and mouth are all entering the fever clinic. There are old directors who will retire, young doctors who have just taken up their posts, and surgical specialists who have put down their knives. Everyone has no time to wait for transformation and adaptation, and you've done a great job.

Every day I look at you in the hospital group, on television fighting figure, also hope that they can recover early to join the battle.

"Sorry, mom and Dad, I haven't had a meal with you this year. "

Narrator: Xiaojing Li, a GP at a hospital in Wuhan

Confirmed infection January 25,2020

Since January of this year, more and more people have been suffering from colds, fevers and coughs. At first, we all thought this was the flu season as usual, but it turned out to be a sudden and violent outbreak of the virus. In January, we admitted three suspected cases of COVID-19 pneumonia, and I caught it in the process because the staff didn't take enough precautions.

On the night of January 19, I returned home with a high fever of 39.5 and was immediately quarantined at home. On January 25, the first day of the Chinese New Year, my nucleic acid test results came back and I was officially diagnosed with COVID-19.

After I was diagnosed, I didn't dare tell my parents at home, for fear that they would worry and lie about working overtime in the hospital. It was not only me that could not accompany them this Spring Festival, but also my brother, who was also a medical worker fighting the epidemic at the front, and The radiology department where they usually contact patients with potential infection, more "dangerous. ".

During my isolation period, my brother would video chat with me to encourage me, the video looked at him, as his sister is very distressed, the last two days he worked continuously for 36 hours, even if the shift rest, he stayed in the hospital near the hotel is also 24 hours on the phone, he said: now patients come to see more, their own on-call, "comrades" need to be able to go back to work at any time.

First-line paramedics

There are many medical workers like my brother. During the isolation period, I saw many of my fellow nurses staying up 24 hours a day, making rounds of the ward. During the isolation period, family members could not be admitted to the hospital to visit them. The nurses took care of the food and clothing of the patients, the first and 10th floors of the hospital buildings were requisitioned, and a doctor and a nurse might have to take care of dozens of patients, at all times at the risk of being infected with the virus, it's swollen or covered in rashes and scratches.

I confirmed the infection or not to hide the news, New Year's Day six, my husband let it slip, the day my father and I video, I saw tears in his eyes, slowly asked me a do not regret being a doctor?

I joke that other people can get infected without being a doctor, so what's there to regret? This job gives me a sense of accomplishment, and I'm willing.

But to tell the truth, I'm also afraid, my parents are old, my own baby is only five months old, but saving lives is a mission given by a white coat, and seeing my teammates still fighting hard, I also want to get well soon, to fight again, and hope the virus goes away, my brother, my parents and my family will be together soon.

-- To Yuen Yuen
